    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, you just said there's a \"growing consensus\" on fairness and rehab. if the sociology community is pretty much in agreement on that, doesn't that mean the \"deterrence\" or \"tough on crime\" argument is basically just an outdated way of thinking? like, is it even a valid policy debate anymore if the evidence shows it's harmful?",
